##Reagent box dilemma: Why is diagnosis so difficult?

Lifeweek

Features an introduction to a magazine and the life he advocates.

The supply side of the kit is adequate production, not "in short supply" , but stuck in the Spring Festival transport capacity, high threshold detection conditions, as well as the approval of related drug qualifications. To this end, the State Food and Drug Administration has recently opened the fast track approval channel.
Reporter | Huang Ziyi, Yan Yan

The supply side of the kit is adequate production, not "in short supply" , but stuck in the Spring Festival transport capacity, high threshold detection conditions, as well as the approval of related drug qualifications. To this end, the State Food and Drug Administration has recently opened the fast track approval channel.

Reporter | Huang Ziyi, Yan Yan

New Year's Eve: 120,000 doses of Kit

▲▲▲

New Year's Eve: 120,000 doses of Kit

▲▲▲

January 24, New Year's Eve, Xiaoyu, Shanghai. On Yindu Road, Longwu road, Minhang district, there was not a single person on the four-lane road. Turning into a park, I saw a building with lights on. From a distance, I saw many people wearing masks, assembling boxes together. The box was small, with a reddish-purple shell that looked like a medicine box from a distance. Such a box is the key to diagnosing COVID-19 pneumonia.

COVID-19 NUCLEIC ACID test kit

These boxes are about to be sent to the Wuhan epidemic area, "nucleic acid test kits" , by Shanghai Geno Biotechnology Company, the company is confirmed by the National Health Commission, one of three reagent production, procurement companies. A box the size of a smartphone can be used by up to 50 people. During the rainy and rainy Lunar New Year's Eve, the relevant staff of Geno told our reporter that the company is working overtime to catch up on the work. A total of 60-70 people are working round the clock. It is expected that the company will be able to complete the production of 120,000 people by the end of the day, no sleep, no rest, more.

In Wuhan, Huanggang, Xiaogan and other places in Hubei Province, where COVID-19 pneumonia is still spreading, the test kits used for diagnosis are in short supply, and large numbers of patients linger outside the hospital gates, unable to be diagnosed in time. In Times of crisis, manufacturers are working overtime to meet emergency needs. In addition to Shanghai Geno, the NHRC also identified Shanghai Berger and Shanghai Huirui as officially recognized suppliers.

"It's going to be an extraordinary New Year's Eve, it's going to be an extraordinary year, " said Wu Yong, a doctor at the University of Florida and Technical Director of Ningbo Heyershi Gene Technology Co. , Ltd. , in a message posted on the social media site shortly before midnight. In the photo, the employees are in the conference room, discussing the test kit with a powerpoint. More than a dozen people attended the meeting, each ordered a KFC take-out as a New Year's Eve dinner. Then, a technician wearing protective clothing, goggles and masks, entered the sterilization room.

COVID-19 is also one of the companies that can produce the test reagent. Wu Yong, clinical diagnostic kit production is a mature industrial system, there are a number of domestic production of IVD NUCLEIC ACID test kit companies. On Dec. 8, the first case was found in Wuhan, and on Jan. 11, when the Scientific Research Institute released its genome sequence information, about 30 manufacturers developed a test kit for COVID-19 within a week. Although the CDC recommends only three companies on its purchasing list, those not on the list are also working overtime.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Extremely Fast R & D and Production Progress, corresponding to the super high demand, from Wuhan as the focus of the country. The shortage of kits is not limited to Wuhan, many hospitals and disease control systems in coastal and southwestern China are stocking up on kits to identify suspected cases, according to a kit maker.

"originally we were preparing for thousands of people per day, but now we may have to increase the production to tens of thousands of people per day, " Wu said, adding that the company's pace is extremely tight and the sales and marketing staff are operating at full capacity, upstream supply chain enterprises also emergency start-up cooperation. In the past week, Hersch has provided tens of thousands of test kits free of charge to hospitals and disease control departments across the country.

Reagent box enterprises are working overtime production, but whether to meet the needs of Wuhan and Hubei Testing? Several companies said the current production and capacity of the kit was by no means an issue. "We can supply Wuhan as much as it needs, " shanghai-based Geno officials have publicly said the company has delivered about 150,000. On New Year's Eve, they passed a special car on the night of January 23 and "drove 20,000 people to the city border of Wuhan, where they were collected by the Wuhan Center for Disease Control and Prevention, " the official told the newspaper.

Other companies have made similar statements. State-commissioned production of Shanghai Huirui bio-media that they have now accumulated production of about 100,000 units of kits, daily output of 20-30,000 units, production end supply is sufficient. Jiangsu Shuoshi biological also said that the company is producing 100,000 people per day to provide the market.

"We don't take a break during the Spring Festival, " Wu said, adding that the company would increase production capacity as necessary later in the year, with a maximum of one million workers a year. If demand picks up later, he said, the company may be able to fill its capacity to supply the market. From the point of view of the quantity of production and supply, the kit is undoubtedly adequate.

Threshold: High Detection Conditions

▲▲▲

Threshold: High Detection Conditions

Yet, with so many kits, why haven't they been used on countless suspected patients?

Logistics is one reason. Many kits need to be transported in the cold chain, but it is the Spring Festival and capacity is tight. Some products are transported by land, while others are transported by air to all parts of the country.

More importantly, the use of kits for testing has a high threshold, the need to equip the relevant laboratory, equipment and technical personnel. "It's not like you can test anywhere with this box, no, " a paramedic said.

According to the prescribed procedures, kits will generally be sent to the provincial CDC, and then issued by the provincial CDC. A person in charge of the Yunnan CDC told This newspaper that for a Emerging Infectious Diseases virus, it should be managed in accordance with the country's Class A regulations for infectious viruses. To avoid contamination, the test must be done at least in a biosafety-level-ii laboratory. "Most hospitals probably don't have it. "

Testing Laboratory, to have negative pressure equipment, air flow can only enter and can not leave; the laboratory of cleanliness, ventilation system, disinfection and sterilization have very high requirements. If you do not have the conditions to do the test, there is likely to be a virus leakage, the laboratory has become a source of contamination. "The regulations now say that in a second-level protective environment, people under the third-level protective measures should be taken, " Wu said. "This is very demanding, meaning that only the third-level hospitals can do the tests, and "small hospitals can't do it. ".

The problem is that Wuhan's current outpatient designated hospitals for suspected cases of COVID-19 pneumonia, mostly small and medium sized hospitals, have no testing conditions. This is the "7 + 7" Insurance System adopted by Wuhan in order to deal with more and more patients, that is, 7 second-level public hospitals are requisitioned to be designated outpatient clinics for fever, and one large general hospital is corresponding to each designated hospital for peer-to-peer support. In order to see a patient in a designated hospital full of patients, you need to help the hospital and even the disease control center to do testing.

In designated hospitals such as Wuhan Red Cross Hospital and Wuhan Hankou Hospital, medical staff said that there were no test kits and test conditions in the hospital, and the hospital had to report high-risk suspected patients. "We have to rely on CDC and Concorde to help us, only they have the conditions, " said a Red Cross hospital staff member.

But in fact, many third-class hospitals do not have similar conditions. Doctors at the Drum Tower Hospital in Nanjing said its laboratory was not up to the test's standard. "There are very few third-class hospitals in Wuhan that can do this, " said a local doctor in Wuhan. Tongji, Xiehe and provincial and municipal centers for Disease Control and Prevention are the main places where tests are available, it is understood. Due to the outbreak, these laboratories are facing a shortage of personnel problems.

In other cities around Wuhan in Hubei Province, the number of hospitals equipped with the test conditions is even more limited, generally concentrated in the city-level hospitals. In Huanggang, for example, according to our reporter, the local announcement of the relevant designated hospitals, there are only 1-2 test conditions and equipment. This means that a large number of grass-roots hospitals in Hubei, which is completely closed to the city, do not have the testing conditions and are out of reach for suspected patients outside the central city area.

A similar situation exists in other parts of the country. A City hospital in Anhui staff said, can do the test of the hospital very few, "basically in Anhui Province fever designated hospitals (a total of 37) , add up to a few. "

Emergency: Special Access Open

▲▲▲

Emergency: Special Access Open

Starting from January 22, the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission said on January 23, has Designated each fixed-point Treatment Hospital, the fever fixed-point diagnosis and Treatment Hospital's counterpart help hospital and the Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention and so on have the condition and the level laboratory to carry out the related test work. The first batch of 10 institutions, is expected to run every day can test nearly 2,000 samples, 30,000 kits will be distributed to designated testing institutions, has been distributed to 6000 people.

This is in order to "in order to adapt to the current situation needs, improve the detection speed" , to the higher-level request the result. Prior to this, the case samples were transferred from the district CDC to the city CDC, and then transferred to the provincial CDC for testing, can test more than 200 samples per day, generally about two days. Wuhan Health Commission also revealed that before January 16, there is no kit in Hubei Province, to be sent to the designated national institutions, the return of about 3 to 5 days. This was one of the reasons for the surge in the number of confirmed cases reported after the 19th.

This also reflects the current situation of the epidemic diagnosis of a dilemma: Many hospitals even if the conditions do not have the qualifications to test. Samples from the hospital were sent to the provincial and municipal centers for Disease Control and prevention for testing, and the results, which would have been available within a few hours, were extended to 2-3 days -- as per the state policy, the hospital can not purchase the new virus test kit directly at present, only the CDC has kits, which has led to a shortage of kits on the hospital side.

The aforementioned Yunnan Disease Control official said that the kit will not be distributed directly to the hospital. In Xiaogan, as the third-class City Center hospital currently has no test kits, and the city's First People's Hospital said the number of test kits to "hair from the top, sometimes yes, sometimes no. "

Another practical dilemma is that for the manufacturer, the supply of the kit to the hospital is required to register with the Drug Administration, but today no one in the country has the relevant qualifications. According to the normal process, if a nucleic acid test kit from the development of the beginning, to obtain the FDA registration certificate, it generally takes 3-5 years. It involves design, validation, product registration, clinical trials, State Food and Drug Administration registration, and so on. It takes a long time and has many processes. At the moment, this process is clearly not sufficient for emergency needs.

To this end, the State Food and Drug Administration recently opened a fast track for approval and initiated an emergency review, according to media reports. A total of seven companies, including three suppliers previously identified by the COVID-19, have tested and approved COVID-19 kits. On January 24, Shanghai Zhijiang Biotechnology Co. , Ltd. passed the test and became the first COVID-19 product to be certified by China's Statutory Inspection Agency. However, it is only the completion of the inspection, has not yet been officially approved listing, follow-up process is still not finished.

The epidemic, however, is not waiting. As the epidemic spread, many manufacturers began to direct for the hospital, the sales staff's phone was directly linked to the Internet, for local governments, hospitals, disease control and consultation. Major Kit Manufacturers are starting to get calls from some hospitals. "We can't even pick up the phone, it's like a war every day, " said a staff member in Shanghai's Huirui Marketing Department.

"This is a special act in an emergency situation, " says one industry source, in which three to five years is now cut to about 15 days.

For some hospitals and patients, the word "confirmed" doesn't mean everything, it just means a number in the official bulletin. Even this number, but also need to be confirmed after the second test unified release. The health care workers at the Anhui Hospital said they had quarantine boxes and all the equipment, and that the health commission would issue a unified report to confirm the diagnosis. "We will not allow the sending of random news, even if the medical conditions and all the equipment are state-of-the-art in the country, " they said

(our intern journalists Yue Ying and Ranger contributed reporting.)
